title: 2015-2025 Police Reports to 21104 Glen Haven Cir, Northville, 48167 MI (Oakland County Sheriff's Office)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Michigan Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

All runs, 911 call transcripts and reports to 21104 Glen Haven Cir, Northville, 48167 MI and 39256 Silverthorne Bnd, Farmington, MI 48331 from 2015-present. I am looking for but not limiting my request to incidents involving Lauren Chipponeri and Cameron Chipponeri.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Bonnie Alfred

title: Obama Presidential Library: Emilie A. Kimball emails (Emilie_A_Kimball@nsc.eop.gov) referencing Yevgeny Prigozhin

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Obama Presidential Library: Emilie A. Kimball emails (Emilie_A_Kimball@nsc.eop.gov) referencing Yevgeny Prigozhin
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Any emails either to or from Emilie A. Kimball's email address (Emilie_A_Kimball@nsc.eop.gov) that that mention the Russian oligarch and founder of the Wagner Paramilitary Group, Yevgeny Prigozhin, in the subject line, email body, or in an attachment.

In order to expedite this request please search for instances where the name Prigozhin appeared in these emails during Kimball's time on the NSC. Limit the search from January 1st 2015 to December 31st 2018. 

Search terms:
Yevgeny Prigozhin
Yevgeny Viktorovich Prigozhin
Евгений Пригожин

If certain parts of this request or certain portions must be redacted please provide any reasonable segregable portion of a requested record after removing or redacting those portions claimed to be exempt, explain in writing the justification for redacting the record, indicate the extent of any redactions on the portion of the record which is made available or published and where technically feasible indicate on the redacted portion itself the specific exemption(s) claimed.

Thank you to the commitment to transparency and I look forward to having this request resolved.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Robert Delaware

title: Obama Presidential Library: Photographs of the February 2014 Irakli Garibashvili/Georgian delegation White House Meeting With Obama

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Obama Presidential Library: Photographs of the February 2014 Irakli Garibashvili/Georgian delegation White House Meeting With Obama
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Any and all photographs taken during a White House meeting between US officials and a delegation from the country of Georgia that visited the White House on February 24th of 2014. Then Prime Minister Irakli Garibashvili was present, and according to news reports President Obama appeared in the meeting for 20 minutes. 

Here's a link to Georgian media news coverage of the event.

https://civil.ge/archives/123532

Please accept this as a request for any photographs from this meeting, with an emphasis on any photos of President Obama taken during this meeting.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Robert Delaware
